#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:1
msgid "Iterative Proportional Representation with Guaranteed Winner"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:2
msgid "Procedure Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:4
msgid ""
"The core of the procedure is an iterative voting process that ensures a "
"party or coalition with a clear governing majority always emerges at the "
"end — without requiring a forced coalition. In contrast to classical "
"majority voting systems, which also produce winners through non-"
"linearity, the votes of the losers are not lost until the last iteration."
" Even those whose party has been eliminated are allowed to vote again on "
"the reduced party list and, if necessary, give their vote to another "
"party still in the race according to the \"lesser evil\" principle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:7
msgid "Step 1: First Proportional Election"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:9
msgid ""
"A normal proportional election is conducted. The parties are ranked by "
"their percentage vote share."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:11
msgid ""
"**Is there a winner?** A party or a voluntarily formed coalition reaches "
"an absolute majority (a pre-defined percentage slightly above 50 %, so "
"that the government remains capable of acting even when individual "
"members are absent) → **Procedure finished.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:12
msgid "**No winner?** → Continue with step 2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:14
msgid "Step 2: Reduction and New Round"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:16
msgid ""
"The vote shares are cumulated starting with the strongest party until "
"**two thirds** of all votes are reached or exceeded. Only the parties "
"included in this sum take part in the next round. All voters — including "
"those whose party has been eliminated — may vote again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:18
msgid "The procedure returns to step 1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:20
msgid "Special Case: Only Two Parties Remaining"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:22
msgid "**First round with two parties:** Round is repeated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:23
msgid ""
"**Second inconclusive round:** A random procedure decides (e.g. minimal "
"percentage differences or drawing of lots)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:25
msgid "Termination"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:27
msgid ""
"The procedure is guaranteed to terminate because the number of competing "
"parties is reduced in each iteration until finally only two remain."
msgstr ""

