#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:43
msgid "Execution in the Simulation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:45
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"In the simulation, an election is started by creating an "
"{class}`~ipres.election.Election` object. The constructor expects an "
"{class}`~ipres.election_config.ElectionConfig` object with the global "
"procedure configuration created in the first step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:47
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The procedure is started using the {meth}`Election.run() "
"<ipres.election.Election.run>` or the {meth}`Election.start() "
"<ipres.election.Election.start>` method. The {meth}`Election.run() "
"<ipres.election.Election.run>` method executes the entire procedure, "
"while the {meth}`Election.start() <ipres.election.Election.start>` method"
" only executes the first round and returns a reference to the executed "
"round. This allows interactive intervention in the voting process, for "
"example to form coalitions or to test the effect of individual "
"parameters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:49
msgid "**Automatic run**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:57
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"A round is represented by an instance of the "
"{class}`~ipres.election_round.ElectionRound` class. The "
"{class}`~ipres.election_round.ElectionRound` class knows whether another "
"round is required or not. If so, it returns the input for the next round."
" This can optionally be overridden manually to specifically test certain "
"use cases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:59
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"A voting round is executed by calling {meth}`ElectionRound.run() "
"<ipres.election_round.ElectionRound.run>`. ({meth}`Election.start() "
"<ipres.election.Election.start>` also calls {meth}`ElectionRound.run() "
"<ipres.election_round.ElectionRound.run>` internally.) The class method "
"{meth}`ElectionRound.run() <ipres.election_round.ElectionRound.run>` "
"takes an {class}`~ipres.election_round.ElectionRoundInput` object as a "
"parameter and returns an {class}`~ipres.election_round.ElectionRound` "
"object with the result of the executed voting round. Depending on whether"
" it was a real election round or a drawing of lots, the result is an "
"instance of {class}`~ipres.ballot.Ballot` or "
"{class}`~ipres.draw_of_lots.DrawOfLots`. Both classes are subclasses of "
"{class}`~ipres.election_round.ElectionRound`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:61
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The procedure is only complete when there is a winner. In this case, "
"{meth}`ElectionRound.hasNext() "
"<ipres.election_round.ElectionRound.hasNext>` returns `False` and "
"{meth}`ElectionRound.hasWinner() "
"<ipres.election_round.ElectionRound.hasWinner>` is `True`. Only then can "
"the election be evaluated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:64
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"By forming coalitions, a round that ended without a winner can "
"retrospectively receive a winner. Coalitions are created by calling "
"{meth}`Ballot.formCoalition() <ipres.ballot.Ballot.formCoalition>`. Note "
"that coalitions can only be formed after a voting round and, once formed,"
" must remain together until the end of the procedure — this ensures that "
"the number of participants is reduced in each round."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:66
msgid ""
"For details on `Contestant` and coalition formation see the notebook "
"[Contestant](../../notebooks/en/contestant.ipynb)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:68
msgid "**Manual run with coalition formation:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:83
msgid "Vote Injection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:85
msgid ""
"By default, the simulation generates votes randomly based on "
"probabilities and turnout from the configuration. For tests, "
"demonstrations, or the analysis of specific scenarios, votes can also be "
"provided as fixed values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:87
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"For the first round, {meth}`Election.start() "
"<ipres.election.Election.start>` accepts an optional `votes` parameter:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:93
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"For subsequent rounds, the method {meth}`ElectionRoundInput.with_votes() "
"<ipres.election_round.ElectionRoundInput.with_votes>` is available on the"
" input returned by {meth}`ElectionRound.getNextRoundInput() "
"<ipres.election_round.ElectionRound.getNextRoundInput>`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:101
msgid ""
"`getNextRoundInput()` returns the prepared input for the next round — "
"carrying over all settings (remaining contestants, threshold, strategy, "
"etc.) but without votes. `with_votes()` adds the desired vote counts and "
"returns a new copy of the input with the specified votes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:103
msgid "For multiple constituencies, pass a nested dict:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:111
msgid "Relevant Configuration Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:113
msgid "`ballot_majority_margin` — Ballot threshold"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:115
msgid ""
"`ballot_majority_margin` controls at what vote share a single round "
"produces a winner (default: 2% above 50% = 52%). It is independent of "
"`parliament_majority_margin`. The margin can be specified in percent "
"(`MarginUnit.PERCENT`) or in seats (`MarginUnit.SEATS`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:117
msgid "`DrawLotsStrategy` — Lot strategy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:119
msgid ""
"When two parties fail to produce a winner in two consecutive rounds, the "
"third round is decided by lot:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:121
msgid "**`DrawLotsStrategy.RANDOM`** *(default)*: uniform random draw."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/iterative_proportional_election.md:122
msgid ""
"**`DrawLotsStrategy.MARGINAL_LEAD`**: The marginal vote difference is "
"treated as a random outcome — the party that happened to receive slightly"
" more votes wins."
msgstr ""

